This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a convolutional neural network (CNN) based method for automatic plaque characterization from intracoronary optical coherence tomography (OCT) images. Additionally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which are common topics in the computer vision field. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Moreover, the paper involves statistical analysis and data mining, which makes it possible to belong to the machine learning (cs.MS) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which makes it possible to belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
